cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms for computing centrality in a two-party setting. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new two-stage stratified sampler for improving time and space efficiency. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper uses real-world social network data sets to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed protocol. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses differential privacy mechanisms to protect sensitive information. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a protocol for computing centrality in a distributed system with two mutually distrusting parties.
